item.title: No Noobies. I need a great compiler
item.dc:creator: @firewithin3 firewithin3
item.description:
@firewithin3 wrote:

Try replacing the code in the run.bat with

@echo off
if exist "%programfiles%\Java" (call :compile "%programfiles%\Java\") else (goto error)
:compile
for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\java.exe")
if defined p (%p% -Xmx512m -cp .;./jython.jar;./MySql/mysql-connector-java-3.0.08-ga-bin.jar server)
if defined p (goto end)
:error
echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load.
"%programfiles%\Internet Explorer\iexplore.exe" http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp
:end
echo Finished!
pause
exit

I made up that code right now, tell me if it works or not.
